    "narrative": "The focal point of today\u2019s lineup is **Tyler Freeman**, who leads our roster with a 71.80 efficiency score against Javier. His favorable park factors (+14%) and SP skill matchup (+17%) make him our primary offensive engine, compounded by an advantageous #2 spot in the order. Joining him at the top of the board is **Bryson Stott** (68.43), whose +13% dynamic platoon edge against Mahle outweighs a slight park penalty, cementing his status as a \"Strong\" start. **Lawrence Butler** (65.36) and **Jonathan Aranda** (64.21) also remain critical contributors; **Aranda** specifically benefits from a massive +12% platoon boost against Rea, ensuring he remains a high-floor play despite the negative park adjustment.\n\nWe have exercised caution with our star power today, notably with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who carries a 55.84 score due to a difficult matchup against the elite Ragans. While his base projection is high, the -19% SP skill penalty suppresses his daily ceiling significantly. The most difficult personnel decision involved **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of a starting berth at 53.41. While he offers a solid floor, the combination of facing a top-tier arm in Nola and the high efficiency of our middle-infield options forced him to the bench. We are also monitoring the risk profile of **Daulton Varsho** (52.66), as his matchup against Ohtani is our most dangerous of the day, resulting in a severe -19% SP skill adjustment.\n\nBeyond the baseline scores, we are tracking the impact of stolen base opportunities. While **Masyn Winn** (61.79) is a \"Strong\" start, his efficiency takes a minor hit (-1.0%) due to the opposing catcher\u2019s elite pop-time, which may stifle his ability to contribute to our scarcest category. **Gleyber Torres** (55.60) represents a volatile play; while he benefits from a +5% wind-out factor in his favor, his -13% platoon penalty against Ober requires careful monitoring throughout the afternoon. We remain disciplined with our bench\u2014including **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Brendan Donovan**\u2014preserving our game caps for matchups with more favorable platoon splits and lower-tier opposing starters.",
